-> fix no audio (dummy device)
https://bbs.archlinux.org/viewtopic.php?id=272060
a quick hack could be trying to enable snd_hda_intel via e.g. /etc/modprobe.d/inteldsp.conf
options snd_intel_dspcfg dsp_driver=1
this will break internal mic support but might at least get you audio out.



-> backlight
https://github.com/haikarainen/light
https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/backlight
(add user to video group and control light with: "light -U" and "light -A")



-> bluetooth stop stealing airpods connection from iphone
https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/bluetooth
in /etc/bluetooth/main.conf
[Policy]
AutoEnable=false



-> libinput fix scroll speed
yay -S libinput-config-git
sudo nvim /etc/libinput.conf
scroll-factor=0.2
